WEBVTT

00:00.160 --> 00:04.560
From the architectonic point of view, this room is conceived lower and narrower.

00:05.680 --> 00:09.680
The presence of irons and shackles testifies the character of this invasion.

00:10.800 --> 00:14.320
The Ottomans infiltrated Europe at the end of 14th century.

00:15.360 --> 00:23.760
In 1372 in Marica, in 1385 in Saver, Lushnia, in 1389 the Battle of Fusha Kosova where the

00:23.760 --> 00:29.200
Albanians were distinguished in an anti-Ottoman coalition, where an Albanian from Kosova named

00:29.200 --> 00:36.560
Milos Kopili succeeded in killing Sultan Maradi I. Kruja was invaded in the year 1415.

00:37.680 --> 00:44.400
This room includes map of the Ottoman invasion, the war cry of Arbor Mosaic,

00:45.520 --> 00:51.520
the fireplace of Castriot, a sword donated to the Ferdinand of Naples reproduction.

00:52.640 --> 00:58.000
At the entrance of unification endurance room are exposed two authentic bells, 14th century.

00:58.960 --> 01:07.440
George Castrioti, 1405-1468, was the youngest son of John Castrioti who was the leader of

01:07.440 --> 01:13.600
the princedom in Middle Albania. His first possessions were two villages in Dibra village,

01:13.600 --> 01:20.400
Senia and Gardi Pashtem. When John Castrioti was under the vassalage of Sultan Maradi II,

01:20.400 --> 01:25.760
he was obliged to give away as hostages his four sons to the Sultan, and George was one of them.

01:26.560 --> 01:32.000
The Ottomans sent him to the military school of Iklans. They named him Iskander, which

01:32.000 --> 01:38.160
corresponds to the Christian name of Alexander. Later, they gave him the military grade Beg,

01:38.160 --> 01:41.200
that is why he is known by the name Skanderbeg.

